channel.title: My Port forwarding does not work!
channel.description:
ok so i have done everthing perfectly followed the video for port forwarding created a no-ip domain went into my dgl-4300 dlink router went into virtual server filled everthing out corectly but when i go to log in to my private server i still get error conecting to server.. i check'd my status on canyouseeme.org and it cannot. somthing i noticed is my ip on my no-ip icon in syste tray is diferent from my ip in my command prompt using ipconfig
n e help would be very much appriciated plz and ty
-real

item.dc:creator: @tomato721 tomato721
item.description:
@tomato721 wrote:

real897j:

still need help!

cuz ur no-ip’s ip is ur EXTERNAL IP your INTERNAL IP is the one in ip-config
your INTERNAL ip is an private ip created by ur router so multiple cpus can connect to the internet without having to register another EXTERNAL ip from ur ISP (internet service provider)

i hope u know sumthing now
